Entertainment One May Buy Chorion Assets, Mail on Sunday Says

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 
2011-09-18T09:21:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/entertainment-one-may-buy-chorion-assets-mail-on-sunday-says.html
Entertainment One Ltd. (ETO) , which owns
the rights to Peppa Pig, has held talks with Chorion Plc about
buying the owner of the Noddy brand’s assets, the Mail on Sunday
 reported , without saying where it got the information.  The talks may have started before Entertainment One said it
was considering selling itself, though it’s still interested in
Chorion, the newspaper reported. The two companies declined to
comment, according to the Mail. 